added test case for quads

passed enumerate_all_melds* tests

Passed tests for meld enumeration
added/passed test__prune_meld_group passed test__examine_melds
split gin.py into ginplayer.py and ginhand.py, along with respective test files. added debug printouts to deadwood_count and _examine_melds corrected deadwood_count for g3 case

Added GinHand.size() Moved GinPlayer into its own file Added test scaffolds for GinPlayer Added second knock listener: one for knocking, one for knocking gin Created GinStrategy Create GinTable, added scaffold seating method
Derived child class of Deck, GinDeck, to allow the Deck class to be reused in other projects

Changed Deck to be new class type (meaning it now inherits from object) to fix a super() call from a child class Fixed a GinDeck.deal_a_card() Added GinHand.get_card_at_index() Began implementation of GinMatch Added DrawException and StrategyExecutionException GinPlayer now has an action member to handle the advice provided from GinStrategy Implemented GinPlayer.draw(), consult_strategy(), pickup_discard() Began implementing GinPlayer.execute_strategy() -- 3/5 cases done We now hold discarded cards in GinTable's discard_pile Created a parameter-driven MockGinStrategy GinTable now holds the active deck Added many test cases for GinPlayer
Added and Passed tests for knock_listener and knock_gin_listener
Cleaned out duplicate seating exception, which is already handled in gintable.py
Added tests for execute_strategy_knock and execute_strategy_knock_gin
Passed execute_strategy_knock and execute_strategy_knock_gin tests
Added and Passed rudimentary test_take_turn
Added and Passed tests for end_with_knock, end_with_knock_gin, deal_cards GinPlayer now keeps track of what table it is seated at Moved Helper (generates CardGroups and GinHands) to its own file

Added test_enumerate_all_melds and test_enumerate_all_sets Changed Helper class to be a baseclass so we can inherit its methods and use asserts in them! Added test_deadwood_cards Added test_process_layoff Clarity rename: player_knocked to player_who_knocked Added Helper.compare_arrays_of_cardgroups
Moved card_data into Helper Added stubs for deadwood_cards and process_layoff Changed all usage of helper generators to be called as inherited members
Simplified test_best_action Standardized enumerate_all_melds_and_sets tests to use new inherited Helper methods
Moved repetitive setup code into setUp()
deleted gin.py -- better code existed elsewhere. comment typo and whitespace cleanup. randomly seat players

Added __repr__() to GinCard and GinCardGroup for better debugging Removed random seating from GinMatch class: it was breaking tests that depended on specific players going first. Added and Passed two test_sort_melds tests Improved assertion in test_helpers
Made Cards sortable via __cmp__() method
Added __cmp__() to GinCardGroup Added GinCardGroup.uniqsort_cardgroup()
Added GinHand.deadwood_cards()
Refactored GinHand to derive from GinCardGroup. All tests pass.
Passed deadwood_cards() Moved all declarations of card_dataX into Helper class
Made GinCardGroup iterable
Passed all cases of test_process_layoff Added some new card_dataX cases for test_process_layoff
Refactored enumerate_all_sets to use uniqsort_cardgroups(). Added clarity in comments.
Refactored enumerate_all_melds to use uniqsort_cardgroups(). Added clarity in comments.
Added and Passed test_notify_of_knock and test_notify_of_knock_gin
Added and passed updated_score_for_knock and update_score_for_knock_gin tests
Refactored play_game into 3 parts: deal_cards(), take_turns() and update_score() Passed tests for all three
Added and Passed test_update_score_with_knock_undercut
Refactored _is_in_a_meld to use fewer return statements Added sanity check to run() Decided to axe the test_play_game() test
Began implementation of neural component. Added Neuron and passed tests: test_attach_my_axon and test_attach_my_dendrite
Added utility debugging function indent_print for easier recursive debugging Added Perceptron and InputPerceptron classes with respective tests Passed respective tests

Renamed EnvironmentObject to Sensable -- intent is to make this a Base class that Card, Hand, etc can inherit from. Renamed EnvironmentSensor to Sensor Added MockSensable and MockSensor Fixed broken tests in TestInputPerceptron

Cleaned up ordering of suits in deal prior to shuffle (cosmetic) Changed (with passed Tests) Player.knock() and .knock_gin() to discard a given card. Fixed TestDeck.testShuffle() Removed last vestiges of camel-casing Added setUp to TestGintable
Added and Passed tests for Wrapper class for the purpose of an Observer pattern
Card, GinTable now inherit from object
Moved Wrapper out of utility and into observer.py

Renamed 'Wrapper' to 'Observable' Settled on an Observer paradigm using Observer.observe() and .register() and Observable.register_observer() Added and Passed tests for Observer.register(), Observable.register_observer()
Moved __repr__() and ranking() from GinCard into Card Added GinCard.ranking()

Added test for Player.organize_data() Changed behavior of Observable to now be a base class. notify_observer() is now a decorator which will wrap a method with notifications to observers. Removed __getattr__ and __setattr__ wrapper behavior Passed all tests.
Added notify_observer decorators to GinPlayer

Removed Sensor and Sensable classes Introduced ability for one Observer to connect to multiple InputPerceptrons (via id and index lookups) Moved observe implementation into Observer. This leaves PlayerObserver fairly empty for now.
Changed knock/knock_gin behavior to discard and notify listeners. Reinstated MockSensor and MockObservable to once again pass the big TestPerceptron.test_generate_output() call
Added Observer.noop_notify to fill the buffer during Observer.__init__
Changed requirement for subclasses of Observable to return a dict through organize_data()

GinMatch now inherits from Observable. Added placeholder for GinMatch.organize_data() Moved GinPlayer.id into Observable Began implementing NeuralNet. Added and passed tests for: __init__, validate_weights, calculate_hidden_count, create_input_layer, create_hidden_layer Removed unused function Perceptron.attach_one_input Renamed 'multiplied' to 'weighted' Added some sanity checks to InputPerceptron.__init__ Created MultiInputPerceptron as a base class for HiddenPerceptron (also for OutputPerceptron, when we get there) Observer.observe now handles empty cases

I lied in last commit. Did not pass test for create_hidden_layer in last commit, BUT WE DO NOW! Better testing for test_create_output_layer Added sensor-input weights into test_generate_output. Need to add the sensor-weights into the by-hand calculations. For now, they're fixed at 1.0
Passed test_create_output_layer

Wrote and passed tests for NeuralNet.pulse() Created debugging tool NeuralNet.print_me() Changed output_layer to be a list of dicts with output_key as the key Created OutputPerceptron to hold an output_key

Cleaned up test_ginplayer, moving lots of things into setUp() Fixed a bug in GinPlayer.take_turn() where we weren't consulting the strategy twice when we had 10 cards. Added GinPlayer.accept_improper_knock Added NeuralGinStrategy class Added NeuralGinStrategy.consider_accepting_improper_knock() to communicate between neural net and player action Added and passed tests for handling the acceptance of improper knocking Added and passed testss for GinStrategy.decode_signal() Added some true/false return functions to Helper that can be monkey patched in Added MockNeuralNetwork Moved some mocks around and updated import statements
Fixed bug in decode_signal() where we were returning an out of bounds index for signal = 1.0 Clarified action name to 'PICKUP-FROM-DISCARD' Added and passed tests for decode_best_action
Added and passed tests for GinMatch.organize_data() Added @notify_observers_after (also renamed existing @notify_observers to a higher-clarity @notify_observers_before)
Added and passed tests for GinTable.organize_data()
Corrected GinTable.organize_data() to not reveal the content of the undealt deck
Decoupled GinTable.deck from Player so we can properly observe changes in GinTable Removed all PlayerObservers and replaced with Observers (just naming semantic)
Updated DrawException to track who caused it. Improved notify_observers* decorators to return the return value of the function they wrap
Added genetic_algorithm.py Added GeneSet, GinGeneSet classes Added and Passed tests for storing genes, crossing and mutation
Created WeightSet to handling how we offer a GeneSet to a NeuralNet Refactored NeuralNet to use WeightSet, rather than raw weights
Added Population function to act as holder/controller of our population and genetic algorithm Passed test for __init__ Added draw function
Added debug logging for GinMatch to watch a game. Added get_player_string

Changed naming for 'sensors' to 'observers' for clarity Modified consult_strategy() to take a phase parameter to split potential actions between phases of turn. We could evolve smartness about this, but it makes testing rougher. It also allows the start/end strategies to more finely tune their own weights. Added an observable_width requirement to Observables in order to more accurately line up weights Changed the player's draw() to use a method that will notify observers Added InvalidPlayError for when a player tries to pickup on the first turn with 11 cards Added Population.cull(), .add_member(), .cross_over(), .get_top_members(), .fitness_test(). Passed all but .fitness_test() Added GinStrategy.decode_index Began observing the gc
Cleaned up some logging messages

Worked on the random initialization of genesets Added limit to number of turns to be taken, as gen=0 specimens like to trade the same discard back and forth forever We now properly clean up the playing space after a game via Player.empty_hand(), GinTable.refresh_deck() Cleaner Logging Fixed a bug where Player.organize_data() only returned 10 indexes when we expected 11 Added some profiling code in playground.py

fitness_test now only matches a geneset against another geneset ONCE (used to do AvsB,BvsA -- now just AvsB) Added random win after X turns Changed ordering of action arrays to better fit with initial geneset conditions
Fixed a bug where we were destructively popping a genelist with the intention of doing it again later on Memoized first layer of generate_output
Refactored GinHand() to take a card, rather than a (rank, suit) tuple Memoized enumerate_all_melds, deadwood_count Added toggle for debug logging to speed things up
Removed GinHand.add() function -- we now use add_card() exclusively to stay away from naked tuples

Refactored @memoized to accept class methods Simplified Card.__cmp__ to use ranking() Optimized GinHand.add_card() to preserve sort order during insertion, thereby eliminating call to sort() Fixed potential bug source where both player_who_knocked and player_who_knocked_gin were simultaneously True More memoization Fixed some tests to go along with new card sort order -- ranking() Simplified compare_arrays_of_cardgroups()
Added new memoization which uses LRU collection Added coinflip decision if we run out of cards

Added generate_next_generation Fixed cull() Added mutation call to cross_over Fixed bug where player2 was always rewarded for a game won by coinflip, even if p1 won the flip Fixed bug where knock_gin's weren't being properly accounted for in update_score()

Implemented local storage for Population Reworked ranking function to focus on non-coinflip wins as a percentage of games played More tracking of game stats Updated playground.py to have SIGINT handling for easier run/stop/analyze cycling Added test case to GinMatch.test_run to track our new game stats Changed MockGinStrategy definitions to have start/end strategies
Changed base mutation rate to 7.5% Moved static random seed into test cases
Fixed division by zero problem by correcting the divisor in the ranking function
Temporarily fixed divbyzero problem by setting a minimum for the divisor in the ranking function
